description:
On Feb 22 Google said "We're already working to address recent issues with Gemini's image generation feature. While we do this, we're going to pause the image generation of people and will re-release an improved version soon.” (see https://x.com/Google_Comms/status/1760603321944121506?s=20). 

This market will resolve to “Yes” if Gemini officially resumes its image generation of people by Feb 29, 2024, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

Note: if some people are still able to use Gemini to generate images of people, it will not suffice to resolve this market to "Yes" - there must be communication from Google or a consensus of credible reporting that Gemini's image generation of people has resumed. 

The primary resolution source will be information from Google and Alphabet, however a consensus of credible reporting will also be used.
